const faqs = [
  {
    question: "When does the missed call text go out?",
    answer: "The text dispatches within seconds of a call going unanswered or reaching your voicemail. The caller receives it almost instantly — before they have started searching for the next glazier on Google. During autumn when sealed unit enquiries peak, this speed keeps you on every homeowner's measurement shortlist."
  },
  {
    question: "What does the text message say?",
    answer: "You write it during setup and update it any time. A typical glazing contractor message reads: 'Thank you for calling [company name]. I am currently on a glazing installation and will return your call at the first opportunity. Reply with your glass requirements for a faster response.' The wording is entirely yours."
  },
  {
    question: "Does this replace AI Phone Answering?",
    answer: "They operate as layered defence. Phone Answering conducts a full conversation and builds a detailed lead — glass type, frame material, number of units, dimensions. Missed Call Text Back catches the rare calls that slip past — a caller who hangs up after two rings, or a signal gap inside a commercial building. Together, every glazing enquiry is captured."
