  subhead="It is 10am on a Tuesday. You are installing a four-panel bi-fold door in a rear extension in Botley — the aluminium frame is set, the threshold sealed, and you are lifting the first toughened glass panel into the track. Each panel weighs forty kilograms. Two calls come in at 10:15 and 10:40. Your phone is in your jacket pocket, draped over a sawhorse in the garden. Without Missed Call Text Back, both callers hear voicemail. One leaves a message. The other hangs up and calls the next glazier. With it, both receive texts within seconds. The first replies: 'Hi — need 4 sealed units replaced in our Victorian terrace in East Oxford. Timber sashes. How soon can you survey?' At 12:30 you read the reply and call. You book a Thursday morning measurement."
